<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,799,824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bickel &amp; Wei" authorityName="Bickel &amp; Wei" authorityYear="1996" box="[801,1144,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subabruptus">
<emphasis box="[801,974,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. subabruptus</emphasis>
Bickel &amp; Wei
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1220,1290,799,824]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">China</collectingCountry>
, but may be separated from the latter by the specialized hypandrium. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bickel &amp; Wei" authorityYear="1996" box="[829,1000,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subabruptus">
<emphasis box="[829,1000,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">A. subabruptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hypandrium is somewhat regular, swollen at base, with 1 long lateral arm which slightly bends inwards (
<bibRefCitation author="Bickel, D. J. &amp; Wei, L." box="[957,1182,871,896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="251 - 277" refId="ref24371" refString="Bickel, D. J. &amp; Wei, L. (1996) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from southwestern China - Part I. Oriental Insects, 30, 251 - 277. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1996.10433845" type="journal article" year="1996">Bickel &amp; Wei 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Zhang, L. &amp; Wang, M. &amp; Zhu, Y." box="[1195,1385,872,896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="111 - 291" refId="ref25610" refString="Yang, D., Zhang, L., Wang, M. &amp; Zhu, Y. (2011) Fauna Sinica Insecta Uol. 53. Diptera Dolichopodidae. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 111 - 291." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[1261,1312,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 71). The specimens were collected near a swamp with abundant vegetation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
